items.title: The AI that scored 95% — until consultants learned it was AI
items.summary: SAP ran a quiet internal experiment to gauge consultant attitudes toward AI . Five teams were asked to validate answers to more than 1,000 business requirements completed by SAP’s AI co-pilot, Joule for Consultants . The results were striking . The experiment has since become a revealing starting point for SAP's push toward the consultant of 2030: a practitioner who is deeply human, enabled by AI .

items.title: GigaTIME: Scaling tumor microenvironment modeling using virtual population generated by multimodal AI
items.summary: Microsoft researchers uncovered hidden cellular patterns that could reshape how we understand and treat cancer . The study was published in Microsoft Research's GigaTIME blog . The post: Scaling tumor microenvironment modeling using virtual population generated by multimodal AI was published by Microsoft Research at Microsoft Research on Tuesday at 10 p.m. ET . items.title: Brand-context AI: The missing requirement for marketing AI
items.summary: Marketers are recognizing that the future of AI is intelligence that understands who you are as a company and why you matter to your customers . When AI systems are supplied with structured inputs about brand strategy, audience insight, and creative intent, the output becomes sharper and more reliable . CMOs who design these context-aware workflows see better performance, stronger creative, and reliable decision-making .

items.title: Tracking every decision, dollar and delay: The new process intelligence engine driving public-sector progress
items.summary: Oklahoma became the first U.S. state to apply process intelligence (PI) technology for procurement oversight . Real-time monitoring replaced multi-year audit cycles . The platform from market-leader Celonis quickly identified more than $10 million of inappropriate spending . “Process for Progress” sees the combination of AI and PI as a powerful way to help governments deliver vital services more cost effectively .

items.title: Anthropic's Claude Code can now read your Slack messages and write code for you
items.summary: Anthropic has launched a Slack integration that lets software engineers delegate coding tasks without leaving Slack . Anthropic's Claude Code has emerged as a surprise revenue engine, generating more than $1 billion in annualized revenue just six months after its public debut . The coding agent continues to barrel toward scale with customers like Netflix, Spotify and Salesforce, Anthropic says .
